+/// Indicates which region of the window is visible. Content falling outside of this mask will not
+/// be rendered.
+///
+/// The mask carries two independent clipping regions:
+/// - `bounds` is the rectangular clip rect. It shrinks with every `intersect` so that nested
+///   rectangular sub-masks (e.g. an editor's text region inside a pane) properly confine
+///   children to their parent's content area.
+/// - `silhouette_bounds + corner_radii` describes the rounded silhouette established by the
+///   nearest `overflow_hidden + rounded_*` ancestor. The silhouette does NOT shrink when
+///   rectangular sub-masks intersect -- if it did, the rounded curves would "follow" the
+///   smaller bounds and alpha-clip descendants at curves whose centers sit inside the descendant
+///   area. Keeping `silhouette_bounds` pinned to the rounded ancestor's original bounds means a
+///   descendant deep inside the silhouette (well past the curve area) is rendered without any
+///   rounded clipping, while descendants near the original outer corners are still clipped by
+///   the silhouette curves at their geometrically correct positions.
+///
+/// An all-zero `corner_radii` reduces the silhouette check to a no-op, matching the legacy
+/// rectangular-only behavior.
 #[derive(Copy, Clone, Debug, Default, PartialEq, Eq)]
 #[repr(C)]
